+	/*
+	 * Controlled RX timing experiment after:
+	 * - route A lane_polarity 6 -> no SOF
+	 * - route A lane_polarity 0 -> no SOF
+	 * - route C -> no SOF
+	 * - upstream OV5647 test pattern -> no SOF
+	 * - pwdn/power-cycle diagnostic matrix -> no SOF
+	 *
+	 * This variant keeps the current best route-A assumptions and changes
+	 * only one receiver-timing field:
+	 * - cil_settletime = 58
+	 *
+	 * The value 58 is an inference from NVIDIA's r36.x DPHY guidance:
+	 * - pix_clk_hz = 58.333 MHz
+	 * - 10-bit Bayer, 2 lanes -> approximate lane bit rate 291.665 Mbps
+	 * - UI ~= 3.43 ns
+	 * - acceptable settle window ~= 105.6 ns .. 179.3 ns
+	 * - midpoint ~= 142.4 ns
+	 * - lp_clock_period = 1 / 408 MHz ~= 2.451 ns
+	 * - midpoint / lp_clock_period ~= 58.1
+	 *
+	 * This does not prove the sensor's actual DPHY timing. It is a narrow,
+	 * traceable experiment to replace auto-calibrate (0) with a single
+	 * explicit mid-range value.
+	 */
